, and burned it at the brook Kidron. </span><span class=\"v14_15_17\"><sup id=\"2Chr.15.17\" class=\"v14_15_17\">17</sup>But the high places were not taken out of Israel. Nevertheless, the heart of Asa was wholly true all his days. </span><span class=\"v14_15_18\"><sup id=\"2Chr.15.18\" class=\"v14_15_18\">18</sup>And he brought into the house of God the sacred gifts of his father and his own sacred gifts, silver, and gold, and vessels. </span><span class=\"v14_15_19\"><sup id=\"2Chr.15.19\" class=\"v14_15_19\">19</sup>And there was no more war until the thirty-fifth year of the reign of Asa.</span></p>\n</div>\n", 
